Description: Raspberry Pi libcamera fork with rpi/pisp pipeline handler (unofficial Ubuntu build)
 Raspberry Pi's fork of the libcamera userspace camera framework, built with
 the rpi/vc4 and rpi/pisp pipeline handlers and IPAs enabled. Required on
 Raspberry Pi 5 to drive the PiSP hardware ISP from userspace; the
 libcamera 0.2.0 shipped by Ubuntu 24.04 predates PiSP support and sees
 zero cameras on Pi 5.
 .
 Ships the cam CLI, GStreamer plugin, V4L2 compatibility layer, IPA modules,
 IMX219/IMX708 tuning files, and the Python bindings used by picamera2.
 .
 This is an unofficial rebuild of upstream sources for Ubuntu on Raspberry
 Pi 5. Not provided or endorsed by Raspberry Pi Ltd.
